WEBVTT

1
00:00:13.225 --> 00:00:14.800
International arrivals.

2
00:00:14.829 --> 00:00:17.636
please proceed directly
to passport control.

3
00:00:17.671 --> 00:00:19.506
All international arrivals should

4
00:00:19.571 --> 00:00:21.172
proceed directly to passport control.

5
00:00:26.712 --> 00:00:28.813
Attention. passengers.

6
00:00:28.847 --> 00:00:31.682
please do not leave
your luggage unattended.

7
00:00:31.717 --> 00:00:33.818
Unattended luggage is subject to collection

8
00:00:33.852 --> 00:00:38.117
and search by airport police.
Thank you for your cooperation.

9
00:00:38.152 --> 00:00:40.821
Hand. please.

10
00:00:45.193 --> 00:00:47.995
Gary Lester.

11
00:00:49.397 --> 00:00:51.698
What's the nature of your visit?

12
00:00:51.733 --> 00:00:54.701
Um... Visiting a friend.

13
00:00:56.905 --> 00:00:59.239
You traveling alone?

14
00:00:59.274 --> 00:01:02.142
Uh. yes. Alone.

15
00:01:02.177 --> 00:01:04.077
Nothing to declare?

16
00:01:04.112 --> 00:01:06.580
No... Sir.

17
00:01:06.614 --> 00:01:08.181
Nothing.

18
00:01:15.823 --> 00:01:18.325
Khartoum to Atlanta.

19
00:01:18.423 --> 00:01:21.926
What's that... 19 hours. give or take?

20
00:01:21.960 --> 00:01:23.961
You must be running on fumes.

21
00:01:26.832 --> 00:01:29.066
What were you doing in Sudan?

22
00:01:29.101 --> 00:01:31.870
Uh... just hanging out.

23
00:01:31.901 --> 00:01:34.569
You know. tourist stuff.

24
00:01:34.604 --> 00:01:36.471
Yeah. fascinating.

25
00:01:36.506 --> 00:01:39.674
Tell me about the bottle.

26
00:01:39.709 --> 00:01:42.010
Um. it's... It's an antique.

27
00:01:42.045 --> 00:01:45.213
It's very precious.

28
00:01:45.248 --> 00:01:46.681
Oh. please.

29
00:01:46.716 --> 00:01:49.084
Don't touch it.

30
00:01:52.021 --> 00:01:54.489
Yeah. the residue test
didn't turn up nothing.

31
00:01:54.524 --> 00:01:56.491
But here's the wrinkle. Mr. Lester.

32
00:01:56.526 --> 00:01:58.226
This ain't my first rodeo.

33
00:02:02.265 --> 00:02:03.999
Look. I'm warning you. man.

34
00:02:04.033 --> 00:02:05.567
this is not a game.

35
00:02:05.602 --> 00:02:08.170
Don't open the bottle.

36
00:02:08.204 --> 00:02:11.306
Please... Please.

37
00:02:18.648 --> 00:02:21.083
The hell?

38
00:02:53.103 --> 00:02:57.005
Synced and corrected by oykubuyuk
www.addic7ed.com

39
00:03:01.157 --> 00:03:02.624
You were right about the park.

40
00:03:02.658 --> 00:03:04.259
This closeness to nature.

41
00:03:04.293 --> 00:03:06.661
the energy. the people.

42
00:03:06.696 --> 00:03:08.063
Yeah.

43
00:03:08.097 --> 00:03:09.498
My senses. they feel heightened.

44
00:03:09.532 --> 00:03:11.333
It's... It's like a...

45
00:03:11.367 --> 00:03:12.834
A drug?

46
00:03:12.869 --> 00:03:14.236
I wouldn't know.

47
00:03:14.270 --> 00:03:16.338
Seriously?

48
00:03:16.372 --> 00:03:18.006
You've never dabbled?

49
00:03:18.041 --> 00:03:19.441
Seriously.

50
00:03:19.475 --> 00:03:21.410
You try having visions like mine.

51
00:03:21.444 --> 00:03:22.577
and see if you're still
interested in dabbling.

52
00:03:22.612 --> 00:03:25.313
I need more control. not less.

53
00:03:25.348 --> 00:03:26.982
Huh.

54
00:03:27.016 --> 00:03:29.651
Well. sometimes control
is about letting go.

55
00:03:29.686 --> 00:03:31.319
Psychic energy is all around us.

56
00:03:31.354 --> 00:03:33.689
It's like a network.

57
00:03:33.723 --> 00:03:36.625
You have the ability
to travel that network.

58
00:03:36.659 --> 00:03:39.127
But you have to lower your walls first.

59
00:03:39.162 --> 00:03:40.829
And then you'll be able to see

60
00:03:40.863 --> 00:03:42.364
how far you can really go.

61
00:03:46.135 --> 00:03:47.703
I see coins.

62
00:03:49.138 --> 00:03:51.106
They're falling all around us.

63
00:03:51.140 --> 00:03:54.142
It's so beautiful!

64
00:04:00.717 --> 00:04:03.619
Pennies from heaven?

65
00:04:03.653 --> 00:04:06.321
Subtle as a serpent.

66
00:04:06.356 --> 00:04:07.723
People have their own unique markers

67
00:04:07.756 --> 00:04:10.492
for when celestial beings are close by.

68
00:04:10.526 --> 00:04:14.296
She's. uh. rather traditional. it seems.

69
00:04:14.330 --> 00:04:16.898
How's she doing? You think she can help us?

70
00:04:16.933 --> 00:04:19.034
Well. she's more than
handled herself this far.

71
00:04:19.068 --> 00:04:21.470
You're putting a lot
of time and effort into her.

72
00:04:21.504 --> 00:04:23.338
Let's hope it's not wasted.

73
00:04:23.373 --> 00:04:25.540
Wouldn't want to go down that road again.

74
00:04:27.276 --> 00:04:30.512
Well. she's as tough as
they come. this one.

75
00:04:30.546 --> 00:04:32.581
And it's just until we can sort out

76
00:04:32.615 --> 00:04:35.717
this. uh. Rising Darkness nonsense.

77
00:04:35.752 --> 00:04:38.387
Then she's free to go on her own merry way.

78
00:04:38.421 --> 00:04:41.023
Unless you scare her off before.

79
00:04:41.057 --> 00:04:43.925
Not everybody's cut out to do what you do.

80
00:04:43.960 --> 00:04:45.927
And not everybody has
the stomach to watch you do it.

81
00:04:45.962 --> 00:04:47.896
Well. then I'll have to go it alone.

82
00:04:47.930 --> 00:04:49.931
Like I always have.

83
00:04:49.966 --> 00:04:51.533
Now. you gonna make me guess?

84
00:04:51.568 --> 00:04:53.769
Or are you gonna tell me what's going on?

85
00:04:53.803 --> 00:04:55.070
I know something is.

86
00:04:55.104 --> 00:04:56.672
Why else would you be here?

87
00:04:56.706 --> 00:04:59.274
I'm not.

88
00:05:13.923 --> 00:05:16.391
Where's Chas?

89
00:05:16.426 --> 00:05:18.760
I told him to fix that cab of his.

90
00:05:18.795 --> 00:05:21.296
Figured we'd work on your training today.

91
00:05:21.331 --> 00:05:23.398
So. how am I doing?

92
00:05:23.433 --> 00:05:26.902
You're showing flashes of precognition.

93
00:05:26.936 --> 00:05:28.370
retrocognition.

94
00:05:28.404 --> 00:05:30.205
clairtangence. You're a real bitsa.

95
00:05:30.239 --> 00:05:31.707
- Come again?
- Uh. a bitsa. you know?

96
00:05:31.741 --> 00:05:33.108
You've got bits of everything in you.

97
00:05:33.142 --> 00:05:34.176
Hold up.

98
00:05:35.612 --> 00:05:37.779
A break-in.

99
00:05:37.814 --> 00:05:39.648
Pretty clumsy one. too.

100
00:05:39.682 --> 00:05:43.585
You might want to stay out here.

101
00:05:43.620 --> 00:05:45.821
The intruder... Whoever or whatever it is...

102
00:05:45.855 --> 00:05:47.089
will still be in there.

103
00:05:47.123 --> 00:05:48.457
How do you know that?

104
00:05:48.491 --> 00:05:50.425
Ol' Jasper went to a lot of trouble

105
00:05:50.460 --> 00:05:52.628
to safeguard everything
contained in these walls.

106
00:05:52.662 --> 00:05:56.098
I almost feel sorry for whatever's inside.

107
00:06:05.542 --> 00:06:08.910
Seriously disgusting.

108
00:06:08.945 --> 00:06:10.512
Khapra beetles.

109
00:06:10.546 --> 00:06:12.948
One of the most destructive
pests in the world.

110
00:06:12.982 --> 00:06:15.984
I'll assume that's not a good sign?

111
00:06:16.019 --> 00:06:17.753
It's a pretty safe bet.

112
00:06:17.787 --> 00:06:18.820
John?

113
00:06:19.787 --> 00:06:22.722
John. is that you?

114
00:06:22.756 --> 00:06:24.625
Well. bugger me.

115
00:06:24.658 --> 00:06:26.960
Gary bloody Lester.

116
00:06:26.994 --> 00:06:30.796
I... I knocked. but nobody was home. So...

117
00:06:30.831 --> 00:06:33.600
You got yourself caught
in the zero gravity trap?

118
00:06:33.634 --> 00:06:35.368
I don't know what you call it. man. I...

119
00:06:35.402 --> 00:06:36.703
Oh!

120
00:06:36.737 --> 00:06:39.372
I just want it to stop!

121
00:06:39.406 --> 00:06:41.708
It's been a long time. Gary.

122
00:06:41.742 --> 00:06:44.777
I haven't seen you since. uh...

123
00:06:44.812 --> 00:06:47.113
- Newcastle.
- Yeah.

124
00:06:47.148 --> 00:06:49.249
I know.

125
00:06:49.283 --> 00:06:51.451
You know. nobody knew where you went. Gaz.

126
00:06:51.485 --> 00:06:53.286
You just vanished.

127
00:06:54.989 --> 00:06:57.757
I had to get away. I needed
to straighten myself out.

128
00:06:57.792 --> 00:06:59.225
Oh. yeah.

129
00:06:59.260 --> 00:07:00.660
Bang-up job you've done of that. mate.

130
00:07:02.696 --> 00:07:04.597
Well. with everything
that happened. you know.

131
00:07:04.632 --> 00:07:08.435
with Astra...

132
00:07:10.304 --> 00:07:13.506
I just needed to escape. man.

133
00:07:13.541 --> 00:07:16.843
Well. good for you. Gary.

134
00:07:18.879 --> 00:07:20.680
Who's Astra?

135
00:07:24.018 --> 00:07:25.919
Well. go on then.

136
00:07:25.953 --> 00:07:28.855
What daft mess have you
gotten yourself into now?

137
00:07:28.889 --> 00:07:30.290
And why is this place

138
00:07:30.324 --> 00:07:33.359
crawling with bugs?

139
00:07:33.394 --> 00:07:34.961
It's bad. John.

140
00:07:34.995 --> 00:07:37.464
It's really bad. But I di...

141
00:07:37.498 --> 00:07:39.465
I didn't mean for it to happen
this way. I swear it.

142
00:07:41.001 --> 00:07:43.970
It started out as a bender.

143
00:07:44.004 --> 00:07:47.874
Uh. then one night turned
into two and then a week.

144
00:07:47.908 --> 00:07:51.444
And then. well.
I... I just got lost in it all.

145
00:07:51.479 --> 00:07:54.180
I don't even know how.
but next thing I know.

146
00:07:54.215 --> 00:07:57.183
I'm in Sudan.

147
00:07:57.218 --> 00:07:59.485
And. uh. I'm looking to get on.

148
00:07:59.520 --> 00:08:03.289
But as soon as I saw him... I knew.

149
00:08:03.324 --> 00:08:06.559
He had these. these containment
markings all over his face.

150
00:08:06.594 --> 00:08:10.163
You know. the power patterns for binding.

151
00:08:10.197 --> 00:08:13.066
Some bastard had trapped a demon in him.

152
00:08:13.100 --> 00:08:16.970
I knew what I had to do.

153
00:08:17.004 --> 00:08:20.406
This was my chance
to make up for Newcastle.

154
00:08:20.441 --> 00:08:22.742
This was my chance

155
00:08:22.776 --> 00:08:25.011
to atone.

156
00:08:27.281 --> 00:08:31.184
It was like an irresistible passion

157
00:08:31.218 --> 00:08:33.753
just seized me.

158
00:08:33.788 --> 00:08:36.189
It wasn't that I wanted to do it.

159
00:08:37.391 --> 00:08:38.691
I needed to.

160
00:08:48.869 --> 00:08:52.505
You should've seen me. John.

161
00:08:52.540 --> 00:08:54.207
You really should've seen me.

162
00:09:14.261 --> 00:09:16.763
I did it. John.

163
00:09:16.797 --> 00:09:20.767
I trapped a demon in a bottle.

164
00:09:22.136 --> 00:09:23.570
Where's the bottle now?

165
00:09:28.642 --> 00:09:30.143
Hey!

166
00:09:30.177 --> 00:09:33.046
What's your problem. man?!

167
00:09:33.080 --> 00:09:35.882
Hey!

168
00:09:38.919 --> 00:09:39.886
What's going on here?!

169
00:09:39.920 --> 00:09:41.988
Hey! What do you think you're doing...?

170
00:09:44.658 --> 00:09:47.227
Hey!

171
00:09:47.261 --> 00:09:48.895
Someone get security! This guy's crazy!

172
00:09:48.929 --> 00:09:51.498
Hey! Hey! What are you doing?!

173
00:10:26.700 --> 00:10:28.068
It looks like the Star of David.

174
00:10:28.100 --> 00:10:29.901
No. this is the Seal of Solomon.

175
00:10:29.935 --> 00:10:32.504
And this is the Taba'at Shlomo.

176
00:10:32.538 --> 00:10:34.406
Also known as the Ring of Solomon.

177
00:10:34.440 --> 00:10:35.673
It was passed down to Solomon

178
00:10:35.708 --> 00:10:36.941
directly from heaven to trap genies.

179
00:10:36.976 --> 00:10:38.576
So. you're gonna put

180
00:10:38.611 --> 00:10:40.278
Gary's genie back in the bottle?

181
00:10:40.313 --> 00:10:42.046
The Taba'at Shlomo has
strong containment magic.

182
00:10:42.081 --> 00:10:44.282
It's perfect for preparing

183
00:10:44.317 --> 00:10:45.683
any demon binding vessel.

184
00:10:45.718 --> 00:10:47.018
Should be sufficient

185
00:10:47.053 --> 00:10:48.586
to clean up that tosser's mess.

186
00:10:50.923 --> 00:10:52.223
You know. he's lucky
to have you as a friend.

187
00:10:54.260 --> 00:10:57.028
He's all right.

188
00:10:57.063 --> 00:10:58.863
He's just bloody hopeless.

189
00:10:58.898 --> 00:11:00.932
Nobody's hopeless.

190
00:11:03.969 --> 00:11:06.471
I wish that were true.

191
00:11:06.505 --> 00:11:08.373
His old man used to have a car dealership

192
00:11:08.407 --> 00:11:10.241
and more money than he could count.

193
00:11:10.276 --> 00:11:12.577
So. Gary always had
everything he ever wanted.

194
00:11:12.611 --> 00:11:14.612
Gary was good for cash and...

195
00:11:14.647 --> 00:11:17.482
well. that's about it.

196
00:11:17.516 --> 00:11:20.785
We had a bit of a crew that used
to run together back then.

197
00:11:20.820 --> 00:11:23.054
Gary was the only one with a car.

198
00:11:23.089 --> 00:11:24.856
So. you used him.

199
00:11:26.926 --> 00:11:28.426
That depends on your
perspective. doesn't it?

200
00:11:28.461 --> 00:11:30.261
Maybe he used us.

201
00:11:30.296 --> 00:11:33.064
bought our friendship.

202
00:11:33.099 --> 00:11:36.134
If there was one thing Gary knew
how to do. it was use.

203
00:11:36.168 --> 00:11:38.937
Back in the day. he used
to love to get high.

204
00:11:38.971 --> 00:11:41.272
Just the party stuff. nothing hard.

205
00:11:41.307 --> 00:11:45.577
But it seems that after Newcastle.

206
00:11:45.611 --> 00:11:48.646
he's graduated to full-blown junkie.

207
00:11:48.681 --> 00:11:50.949
You want to tell me about Newcastle?

208
00:11:50.983 --> 00:11:52.951
It's a town in the north of England.

209
00:11:52.985 --> 00:11:54.319
Horrible weather

210
00:11:54.353 --> 00:11:57.088
and even worse football team.

211
00:11:57.123 --> 00:11:59.858
You don't end up like Gary
over bad weather.

212
00:11:59.892 --> 00:12:02.594
Well. that's just him. isn't it?

213
00:12:02.628 --> 00:12:04.929
Gary's had more opportunities
handed to him in his life

214
00:12:04.964 --> 00:12:06.431
than I've had hot dinners.

215
00:12:06.465 --> 00:12:08.800
And he's pissed them all away.

216
00:12:08.834 --> 00:12:10.568
Gary's is a life wasted.

217
00:12:14.840 --> 00:12:18.510
B'hoah Shlomoh. kvosh et hahosheh.

218
00:12:20.880 --> 00:12:23.148
All done.

219
00:12:23.182 --> 00:12:26.851
Now all we got to do is
find the bastard demon.

220
00:13:10.696 --> 00:13:12.998
- How come she gets whatever she wants?
- Shh.

221
00:13:13.032 --> 00:13:14.099
She's over there!

222
00:13:14.133 --> 00:13:16.334
Ma'am. you cannot be doing that!

223
00:13:20.539 --> 00:13:21.706
I'm hungry!

224
00:13:21.741 --> 00:13:23.441
I need help!

225
00:13:30.549 --> 00:13:32.917
It is not yet known whether the virus is

226
00:13:32.952 --> 00:13:35.754
transmitted via these insects
or person to person.

227
00:13:35.788 --> 00:13:38.089
There is. however. little doubt

228
00:13:38.124 --> 00:13:40.291
that this outbreak could
mushroom. and rapidly...

229
00:13:40.326 --> 00:13:42.427
The gift that keeps on giving. eh. Gaz?

230
00:13:42.461 --> 00:13:44.929
Suggest that the victims
were gorging on food

231
00:13:44.964 --> 00:13:46.398
just prior to their sudden deaths.

232
00:13:46.432 --> 00:13:49.901
Diagnostic tests are underway
on these vic...

233
00:13:49.935 --> 00:13:52.270
Sounds like a hunger demon.

234
00:13:52.304 --> 00:13:54.773
Nasty mindless bastards with no thought

235
00:13:54.807 --> 00:13:57.375
other than to consume to excess.

236
00:13:57.410 --> 00:13:58.443
Sound familiar?

237
00:13:58.477 --> 00:13:59.911
I'm clean now. John.

238
00:13:59.945 --> 00:14:01.479
and it's gonna stay that way. I swear.

239
00:14:01.514 --> 00:14:04.316
Oh. leave it out. Gaz.
I don't have the time.

240
00:14:04.350 --> 00:14:06.217
That thing's gonna eat its way
through the heart of the city.

241
00:14:06.252 --> 00:14:08.219
one poor wretch at a time.
unless I stop it.

242
00:14:08.254 --> 00:14:10.755
I'm coming with you.
Are you taking the piss?

243
00:14:10.790 --> 00:14:12.657
- It's my responsibility. 
- Forget it.

244
00:14:12.692 --> 00:14:16.461
You're the last person I
want by my side on this.

245
00:14:17.963 --> 00:14:19.464
On anything.

246
00:14:20.766 --> 00:14:22.233
Do us a favor. will you?

247
00:14:22.268 --> 00:14:23.535
Watch over him.

248
00:14:25.171 --> 00:14:26.504
John.

249
00:14:26.539 --> 00:14:28.106
John.

250
00:14:28.140 --> 00:14:29.474
You know. I don't see a lot of people

251
00:14:29.508 --> 00:14:30.608
lining up to lend you a hand.

252
00:14:31.811 --> 00:14:33.478
Maybe you should accept his help.

253
00:14:33.512 --> 00:14:35.246
- People can change. you know?
- Bollocks.

254
00:14:35.281 --> 00:14:37.949
We are who we are.

255
00:14:37.984 --> 00:14:39.484
Eventually.

256
00:14:45.291 --> 00:14:47.993
There he goes again.

257
00:14:48.027 --> 00:14:51.963
Charging head first
into the face of danger.

258
00:14:51.998 --> 00:14:54.366
Is that what happened at Newcastle?

259
00:14:54.400 --> 00:14:56.434
John doesn't seem to want to talk about it.

260
00:14:56.469 --> 00:15:00.038
Too much pain.

261
00:15:00.072 --> 00:15:02.040
Same reason I got into the junk...

262
00:15:02.074 --> 00:15:04.442
try to forget.

263
00:15:04.477 --> 00:15:05.644
Thing like that...

264
00:15:07.680 --> 00:15:09.314
you don't ever forget.

265
00:15:11.484 --> 00:15:13.285
Back then. we all thought
John was the duck's nuts.

266
00:15:13.319 --> 00:15:16.054
I mean. some of the crew were
interested in the occult.

267
00:15:16.088 --> 00:15:19.324
but most of us just wanted
to be around him.

268
00:15:19.358 --> 00:15:23.662
So when he started talking
about this trip to Newcastle.

269
00:15:23.696 --> 00:15:26.298
we all jumped at the chance.

270
00:15:26.332 --> 00:15:31.169
Road trip. some black magic
with the John Constantine.

271
00:15:31.203 --> 00:15:34.272
Who could say no?

272
00:15:35.875 --> 00:15:38.410
But then there was this girl.

273
00:15:38.444 --> 00:15:41.813
She was a daughter
of one of John's friends.

274
00:15:41.847 --> 00:15:44.482
She was possessed.

275
00:15:44.517 --> 00:15:48.853
Nobody knew what to do. how to save her.

276
00:15:48.888 --> 00:15:50.922
John?

277
00:15:50.957 --> 00:15:52.757
He had a plan.

278
00:15:52.792 --> 00:15:54.659
Astra?

279
00:15:54.694 --> 00:15:57.996
I heard you mention that name before.

280
00:15:58.030 --> 00:15:59.464
What happened to her?

281
00:16:05.871 --> 00:16:09.040
Hey. man.

282
00:16:09.075 --> 00:16:14.245
I'm sure you did what you could.

283
00:16:14.280 --> 00:16:16.748
You cared enough to try.
and that's what counts.

284
00:16:20.319 --> 00:16:21.553
Gary!

285
00:17:10.020 --> 00:17:11.555
Excuse me.

286
00:17:11.620 --> 00:17:13.587
You mind if I ask you a few questions?

287
00:17:13.622 --> 00:17:15.923
I already told everybody...
We didn't see anything.

288
00:17:15.957 --> 00:17:18.259
Look. I know what you're thinking.

289
00:17:18.293 --> 00:17:20.027
If I tell this guy what I saw.

290
00:17:20.061 --> 00:17:21.262
he's gonna think I'm crazy. right?

291
00:17:21.296 --> 00:17:22.630
Look. we just want to go home.

292
00:17:22.664 --> 00:17:23.731
Please.

293
00:17:23.765 --> 00:17:25.499
Two minutes. that's all I need.

294
00:17:26.968 --> 00:17:29.804
There were bugs.

295
00:17:31.073 --> 00:17:32.940
Lots of bugs.

296
00:17:32.974 --> 00:17:34.241
Is that so?

297
00:17:35.644 --> 00:17:37.878
When the woman died.

298
00:17:37.913 --> 00:17:40.748
they just came up out of her. like a swarm.

299
00:17:40.782 --> 00:17:42.750
I mean. most people had run off by then.

300
00:17:42.784 --> 00:17:44.251
but we were still there.

301
00:17:44.286 --> 00:17:47.121
What happened to them
after they left the woman?

302
00:17:47.155 --> 00:17:49.256
Well. that's where it gets real crazy

303
00:17:49.291 --> 00:17:51.325
because they just flew into a swarm

304
00:17:51.359 --> 00:17:52.927
and then there was this guy. this. uh...

305
00:17:52.961 --> 00:17:54.228
a meat delivery guy.

306
00:17:54.262 --> 00:17:56.297
and they all just flew right into him.

307
00:17:56.331 --> 00:17:58.065
You happen to catch the name of the company

308
00:17:58.100 --> 00:17:59.133
the delivery guy worked for?

309
00:18:01.770 --> 00:18:03.637
There was a pig and a cow
dancing on his shirt.

310
00:18:03.672 --> 00:18:05.639
Dancing. were they?

311
00:18:05.674 --> 00:18:07.675
Wow. that's something I'd like to see.

312
00:18:08.510 --> 00:18:10.678
Thanks a lot.

313
00:18:20.188 --> 00:18:23.190
You wouldn't be laughing if you
knew what was in store for you.

314
00:18:36.738 --> 00:18:39.306
Is there anyone in here?

315
00:19:29.358 --> 00:19:33.094
Ah. this gets more fun by the second.

316
00:19:33.128 --> 00:19:36.063
Anyone in here still alive?

317
00:19:36.098 --> 00:19:37.798
Preferably not possessed
and feeling peckish?

318
00:19:42.871 --> 00:19:44.071
Hello.

319
00:19:45.807 --> 00:19:46.974
Uh. Jo.

320
00:19:47.976 --> 00:19:49.744
Well. we can chat later.

321
00:19:49.778 --> 00:19:52.580
but right now I'm addressing
the entity inside you.

322
00:19:59.755 --> 00:20:02.056
Melech Eloheem...

323
00:20:02.090 --> 00:20:04.759
haboreh vehayotzer pokehz ahleyhah.

324
00:20:05.961 --> 00:20:07.228
Shmah nah yeshoot...

325
00:20:33.155 --> 00:20:34.755
Bollocks.

326
00:21:04.019 --> 00:21:05.586
How the bloody hell

327
00:21:05.620 --> 00:21:07.355
did a scuzzy little toe rag like you manage

328
00:21:07.389 --> 00:21:09.023
to capture a thing like that?

329
00:21:09.057 --> 00:21:11.092
What happened?

330
00:21:11.126 --> 00:21:12.893
You okay?

331
00:21:13.895 --> 00:21:15.363
Are you okay. more like?

332
00:21:15.397 --> 00:21:17.565
I'm fine.

333
00:21:19.134 --> 00:21:21.268
You find it. the demon?

334
00:21:21.303 --> 00:21:24.705
You sure know how to pick them. Gary.

335
00:21:26.341 --> 00:21:28.709
May be the Rising Darkness. but. uh.

336
00:21:28.744 --> 00:21:31.579
it's stronger than any hunger
demon I've ever encountered.

337
00:21:36.585 --> 00:21:38.219
I've trapped it for now.

338
00:21:38.253 --> 00:21:40.187
but it'll be loose again soon enough.

339
00:21:40.222 --> 00:21:43.124
We need to identify it
with absolute certainty

340
00:21:43.158 --> 00:21:44.358
to put it down for good.

341
00:21:44.393 --> 00:21:46.027
You know. maybe...

342
00:21:46.061 --> 00:21:48.729
maybe this will help.

343
00:21:53.669 --> 00:21:56.337
There's no "maybe" about it. luv.

344
00:21:56.371 --> 00:21:57.738
If they're authentic.

345
00:21:57.773 --> 00:21:59.573
Well. earlier today.

346
00:21:59.608 --> 00:22:01.042
Gary and I. we touched.

347
00:22:01.076 --> 00:22:03.377
and I experienced a...

348
00:22:03.412 --> 00:22:05.146
a psychic transference.

349
00:22:05.180 --> 00:22:07.214
You. uh...

350
00:22:07.249 --> 00:22:08.649
touched?

351
00:22:08.684 --> 00:22:10.584
No. No. no. not like that.

352
00:22:10.619 --> 00:22:12.553
I mean. we only touched
for. like. a second.

353
00:22:12.587 --> 00:22:14.155
But the connection...

354
00:22:14.189 --> 00:22:15.556
it wasn't like I was just in his head.

355
00:22:15.590 --> 00:22:16.824
'cause it was deeper than that.

356
00:22:16.858 --> 00:22:18.225
I felt his pain

357
00:22:18.260 --> 00:22:20.227
and his guilt

358
00:22:20.262 --> 00:22:21.696
and his addiction.

359
00:22:21.730 --> 00:22:23.064
And after...

360
00:22:23.098 --> 00:22:25.132
His withdrawal symptoms.

361
00:22:26.902 --> 00:22:29.837
You got all the lows and none of the highs.

362
00:22:29.871 --> 00:22:32.173
Rough deal. I'd say.

363
00:22:32.207 --> 00:22:33.774
It's probably best

364
00:22:33.809 --> 00:22:35.676
if you two kids keep
your hands to yourself.

365
00:22:35.711 --> 00:22:37.078
For now.

366
00:22:37.112 --> 00:22:38.713
All right?

367
00:22:40.816 --> 00:22:43.117
I'm off to see a man about a dog.

368
00:22:44.486 --> 00:22:48.723
Or. rather. a shaman about a bloody demon.

369
00:23:04.716 --> 00:23:05.916
Not hungry?

370
00:23:05.951 --> 00:23:07.651
Not particularly. mate.

371
00:23:07.686 --> 00:23:09.019
I expected you sooner.

372
00:23:09.054 --> 00:23:11.689
The goat entrails indicated yesterday

373
00:23:11.723 --> 00:23:12.690
as your time of arrival.

374
00:23:14.392 --> 00:23:16.494
Well. don't believe
everything you read. Nommo.

375
00:23:16.528 --> 00:23:18.996
Check out today's Inquirer.
and they'll have you

376
00:23:19.030 --> 00:23:20.898
believing a virus is sweeping the city.

377
00:23:20.932 --> 00:23:22.867
But you know better.

378
00:23:22.901 --> 00:23:24.235
Mm.

379
00:23:24.269 --> 00:23:26.337
Not about most things. but. uh...

380
00:23:26.371 --> 00:23:28.272
afraid it's less a case of

381
00:23:28.306 --> 00:23:29.707
runny nose.

382
00:23:29.741 --> 00:23:31.509
more a case of nasty hunger demon.

383
00:23:31.543 --> 00:23:34.044
The problem's contained for the moment.

384
00:23:34.079 --> 00:23:35.813
but I need answers to finish it off.

385
00:23:38.383 --> 00:23:40.584
We've traced it back as far as Sudan.

386
00:23:40.619 --> 00:23:43.053
but we're not sure
if that's where it originated.

387
00:23:43.088 --> 00:23:45.055
Sudan? Mmm.

388
00:23:45.090 --> 00:23:46.590
Khartoum.

389
00:23:48.126 --> 00:23:49.794
Used to call this poor sod home

390
00:23:49.828 --> 00:23:51.595
before it flew the coop.

391
00:23:54.332 --> 00:23:56.867
Demon you seek is called Mnemoth.

392
00:23:56.902 --> 00:23:59.069
How do we stop it?

393
00:23:59.104 --> 00:24:00.938
I don't know.

394
00:24:00.972 --> 00:24:03.140
There's a way for us
to discover it together.

395
00:24:03.175 --> 00:24:06.076
but it requires some... Travel.

396
00:24:08.814 --> 00:24:11.615
So. by "travel." you mean "trip."

397
00:24:11.650 --> 00:24:12.917
A shared vision.

398
00:24:12.951 --> 00:24:14.151
I can guide you through it.

399
00:24:14.186 --> 00:24:15.419
but you need to see it

400
00:24:15.454 --> 00:24:17.588
the way I do. through my eyes.

401
00:24:17.622 --> 00:24:20.724
It's been a while since
I've taken any psychedelics.

402
00:24:20.759 --> 00:24:22.693
Most of them make me puke these days.

403
00:24:25.263 --> 00:24:26.597
This isn't most psychedelics.

404
00:24:26.631 --> 00:24:27.898
The Mist may well be

405
00:24:27.933 --> 00:24:30.234
the most powerful drug in the world.

406
00:24:30.268 --> 00:24:32.603
Once taken. its effects last forever.

407
00:24:34.039 --> 00:24:35.272
Well. you know me...

408
00:24:35.307 --> 00:24:36.740
I'm game for a laugh.

409
00:24:36.775 --> 00:24:38.810
but forever seems a bit excessive. no?

410
00:24:38.875 --> 00:24:40.176
The Nectar of Nhialic.

411
00:24:40.475 --> 00:24:42.309
A natural counteragent.

412
00:24:53.988 --> 00:24:55.623
Oh... Bloody hell.

413
00:24:55.657 --> 00:24:57.391
That is heinous.

414
00:24:57.425 --> 00:24:59.059
An acquired taste. certainly.

415
00:24:59.094 --> 00:25:00.294
So...

416
00:25:00.328 --> 00:25:03.363
if we're tripping balls.

417
00:25:03.398 --> 00:25:05.566
how do we know to take the nectar?

418
00:25:24.986 --> 00:25:27.988
Call it a hunch. but. uh...

419
00:25:28.022 --> 00:25:31.125
I think this might be working.

420
00:25:50.612 --> 00:25:53.447
Mnemoth has always been with us.

421
00:25:53.481 --> 00:25:55.582
Through all the famines.

422
00:25:55.617 --> 00:25:56.950
the hunger of the starving masses

423
00:25:56.985 --> 00:25:59.586
gave the spirit strength.

424
00:25:59.621 --> 00:26:01.021
Nothing could satisfy the demon's appetite.

425
00:26:01.056 --> 00:26:02.456
After consuming a body.

426
00:26:02.490 --> 00:26:04.992
it moved on to the next.

427
00:26:05.026 --> 00:26:07.027
leaving a growing trail of death.

428
00:26:07.062 --> 00:26:08.662
The shaman couldn't sit by

429
00:26:08.697 --> 00:26:11.365
and watch his people starve.

430
00:26:11.399 --> 00:26:13.133
He could see what no one else could.

431
00:26:13.168 --> 00:26:15.869
This was the evil work of a dark spirit.

432
00:26:15.904 --> 00:26:17.171
He faced

433
00:26:17.205 --> 00:26:18.806
an impossible choice.

434
00:26:18.840 --> 00:26:20.975
for they were all his children.

435
00:26:21.009 --> 00:26:24.111
There was only one way to stop it.

436
00:26:24.145 --> 00:26:26.714
The demon was invited to enter the boy

437
00:26:26.748 --> 00:26:28.882
whom the shaman offered as a sacrifice.

438
00:26:29.984 --> 00:26:32.619
The sacred kusa knife.

439
00:26:32.654 --> 00:26:33.854
Used for the scarification.

440
00:26:33.888 --> 00:26:35.856
Passed down by generations of shaman.

441
00:26:35.890 --> 00:26:40.027
centuries of powerful magic
contained within.

442
00:26:42.163 --> 00:26:44.698
The tongue had to be removed

443
00:26:44.733 --> 00:26:46.667
so the shaman could not be
cursed for what he did.

444
00:26:50.505 --> 00:26:52.406
The pattern...

445
00:26:52.440 --> 00:26:54.408
had to be precise.

446
00:27:06.121 --> 00:27:08.088
Mnemoth could not resist the offering.

447
00:27:08.123 --> 00:27:10.057
Upon entering the boy.

448
00:27:10.091 --> 00:27:12.192
it began consuming him.

449
00:27:12.227 --> 00:27:13.861
but as the demon was now
trapped by the containment

450
00:27:13.895 --> 00:27:15.496
markings. the shaman left.

451
00:27:15.530 --> 00:27:17.698
knowing it would ultimately

452
00:27:17.732 --> 00:27:19.733
consume the boy and itself.

453
00:27:25.040 --> 00:27:26.240
Decent plan.

454
00:27:26.274 --> 00:27:28.876
Shame it didn't stick.

455
00:27:28.910 --> 00:27:31.011
I mean...

456
00:27:31.046 --> 00:27:33.714
what are the odds the kid lands himself

457
00:27:33.748 --> 00:27:35.049
in the one bloody alley

458
00:27:35.083 --> 00:27:37.618
that Gary Lester stumbles into?

459
00:27:43.658 --> 00:27:45.459
Take it slowly. my friend.

460
00:27:45.493 --> 00:27:47.227
Ah. don't worry. mate.

461
00:27:47.262 --> 00:27:49.129
It's not my first disco.

462
00:27:50.999 --> 00:27:53.634
So. the headline here is. uh...

463
00:27:53.668 --> 00:27:56.270
I'm gonna need one of
those fancy blades. right?

464
00:27:56.304 --> 00:27:58.205
The sacred Kusa.

465
00:27:58.240 --> 00:28:00.074
Good luck finding one in this town.

466
00:28:00.108 --> 00:28:03.978
Well. we wouldn't want to make
things easy. now. would we?

467
00:28:08.850 --> 00:28:10.084
I'm sorry. I just...

468
00:28:10.118 --> 00:28:13.320
feel... Sort of trapped in here.

469
00:28:14.650 --> 00:28:16.183
Useless.

470
00:28:16.218 --> 00:28:18.719
Just concentrate on feeling better.

471
00:28:18.754 --> 00:28:20.388
John can handle the rest.

472
00:28:20.422 --> 00:28:21.857
Come on. Gary.

473
00:28:21.922 --> 00:28:23.256
There's nothing for you to do.

474
00:28:23.290 --> 00:28:25.024
I beat that demon once.

475
00:28:26.193 --> 00:28:28.528
I can do it again.

476
00:28:30.497 --> 00:28:32.365
No.

477
00:28:33.300 --> 00:28:35.201
No.

478
00:28:39.673 --> 00:28:41.741
I didn't want to do this.

479
00:28:41.775 --> 00:28:43.610
but you didn't give me a choice.

480
00:28:43.644 --> 00:28:46.813
It's my fault that thing's out there.

481
00:28:46.847 --> 00:28:49.449
It's my responsibility to stop it.

482
00:28:49.483 --> 00:28:51.751
Sorry.

483
00:29:08.947 --> 00:29:12.147
Zed? Gary?

484
00:29:14.852 --> 00:29:16.286
What'd I tell you two

485
00:29:16.320 --> 00:29:18.154
about keeping your hands to yourselves?

486
00:29:19.523 --> 00:29:21.524
You're not as funny as you think.

487
00:29:25.529 --> 00:29:27.163
Oh. no. no. no. no. Take it easy.

488
00:29:27.198 --> 00:29:29.399
Take it easy.

489
00:29:32.269 --> 00:29:34.003
What happened?

490
00:29:37.341 --> 00:29:39.008
Bastard!

491
00:29:39.043 --> 00:29:40.210
He just...

492
00:29:40.244 --> 00:29:42.212
he just wants to help.

493
00:29:42.246 --> 00:29:44.380
He's so racked with guilt

494
00:29:44.415 --> 00:29:47.317
that he's going after the demon himself.

495
00:29:47.351 --> 00:29:50.487
- Told you that. did he?
- Yes. he did.

496
00:29:50.521 --> 00:29:52.589
And he meant it. 'Cause I felt it.

497
00:29:52.623 --> 00:29:55.492
That's not what's happening. trust me.

498
00:29:55.526 --> 00:29:57.160
Why do you always want to see
the worst in people?

499
00:29:57.194 --> 00:29:59.829
I see the truth.

500
00:29:59.864 --> 00:30:03.032
Gary's hopelessly addicted to heroin.

501
00:30:03.067 --> 00:30:05.702
And let me give you
a little tip about addicts:

502
00:30:05.736 --> 00:30:08.471
between thought and action
comes temptation.

503
00:30:09.607 --> 00:30:11.341
Always.

504
00:30:16.814 --> 00:30:18.715
Ooh. nice one. lads.

505
00:30:18.749 --> 00:30:20.283
Think I just heard a rib crack.

506
00:30:20.317 --> 00:30:21.618
Oh. no. no. no. no.

507
00:30:21.652 --> 00:30:23.353
Don't stop on my account.

508
00:30:23.387 --> 00:30:25.388
In fact. maybe I can help.

509
00:30:27.324 --> 00:30:29.726
I'm guessing that this
little misunderstanding

510
00:30:29.760 --> 00:30:31.561
has something to do with the
purchase of narcotics. correct?

511
00:30:33.464 --> 00:30:36.432
Best high you'll ever have.

512
00:30:37.268 --> 00:30:38.435
On my life.

513
00:30:43.674 --> 00:30:46.643
Must be getting soft.

514
00:30:46.677 --> 00:30:48.411
Should've let those two keep going on you.

515
00:30:48.445 --> 00:30:49.646
Get you out of my hair

516
00:30:49.680 --> 00:30:51.414
for good.

517
00:30:51.449 --> 00:30:53.249
So why didn't you?

518
00:30:55.152 --> 00:30:57.020
You are a massive pain
in the arse. Gary Lester.

519
00:30:58.355 --> 00:31:01.090
But you're still my mate.

520
00:31:01.125 --> 00:31:02.826
More's the pity.

521
00:31:04.528 --> 00:31:06.663
Friends don't betray each other.

522
00:31:11.202 --> 00:31:12.535
I betrayed you.

523
00:31:14.004 --> 00:31:15.672
I betrayed her.

524
00:31:15.706 --> 00:31:17.073
Oh. don't worry about Zed.

525
00:31:17.107 --> 00:31:18.408
She's a tough bird. that one.

526
00:31:18.442 --> 00:31:20.143
I'm talking about Astra.

527
00:31:27.384 --> 00:31:29.786
There's something I need to tell you. John.

528
00:31:31.622 --> 00:31:32.856
About Newcastle.

529
00:31:34.358 --> 00:31:36.726
Gaz. you don't... Please.

530
00:31:37.962 --> 00:31:39.896
I need to say this.

531
00:31:42.533 --> 00:31:44.534
I was high.

532
00:31:45.970 --> 00:31:47.971
Been smoking all day.

533
00:31:50.041 --> 00:31:52.942
By the time the séance started...

534
00:31:55.079 --> 00:31:57.847
I was well caned.

535
00:31:57.882 --> 00:32:00.517
And then. when...

536
00:32:00.551 --> 00:32:04.454
everything started going pear-shaped...

537
00:32:04.488 --> 00:32:06.022
I hid.

538
00:32:10.027 --> 00:32:12.562
Under a bed in a room upstairs.

539
00:32:12.596 --> 00:32:15.031
Her screams...

540
00:32:15.066 --> 00:32:17.066
I can still hear them. John.

541
00:32:17.101 --> 00:32:19.502
She was being dragged to Hell.

542
00:32:21.072 --> 00:32:23.239
I just laid there in me own stinkin' piss.

543
00:32:23.274 --> 00:32:26.576
closed me eyes. covered me ears...

544
00:32:26.610 --> 00:32:28.511
and when it was all done...

545
00:32:30.448 --> 00:32:32.849
I ran.

546
00:32:35.753 --> 00:32:39.589
John?

547
00:32:39.623 --> 00:32:43.059
Say something. please.

548
00:32:43.093 --> 00:32:45.862
Wasn't your fault. mate.

549
00:32:45.896 --> 00:32:49.199
Should've never gotten you all involved.

550
00:32:49.233 --> 00:32:51.167
You. especially.

551
00:32:51.202 --> 00:32:52.769
Because I'm a coward.

552
00:32:52.803 --> 00:32:54.738
Because it's not your world.

553
00:32:54.772 --> 00:32:57.407
Never was and I knew it.

554
00:32:57.441 --> 00:33:00.410
And I knew you were high.

555
00:33:00.444 --> 00:33:02.946
We all did.

556
00:33:02.980 --> 00:33:05.615
The thing is. Gaz...

557
00:33:05.649 --> 00:33:08.118
I don't blame you.

558
00:33:08.152 --> 00:33:11.554
I never did.

559
00:33:11.589 --> 00:33:14.324
You had every right to be afraid.

560
00:33:17.394 --> 00:33:18.828
And you know what I always say. Gaz?

561
00:33:20.631 --> 00:33:23.967
Everyone has the capacity to change.

562
00:33:24.001 --> 00:33:26.403
I've never heard you say that before.

563
00:33:26.437 --> 00:33:29.172
Exactly.

564
00:33:31.942 --> 00:33:33.577
We're live outside the Fox Theater

565
00:33:33.611 --> 00:33:35.712
in mid-town Atlanta.
which is now on lockdown.

566
00:33:35.746 --> 00:33:38.381
following reports
of another virus outbreak.

567
00:33:38.416 --> 00:33:41.751
Get it in you. mate.

568
00:33:42.953 --> 00:33:44.554
We've got a demon to catch.

569
00:33:44.588 --> 00:33:47.424
Together.

570
00:33:57.468 --> 00:33:58.802
Nothing too elaborate.

571
00:33:58.836 --> 00:34:01.971
Just a simple distraction.

572
00:34:03.474 --> 00:34:05.442
Then what?

573
00:34:05.476 --> 00:34:08.011
Then you break in
and steal the bloody Kusa knife.

574
00:34:09.677 --> 00:34:12.212
It's not rocket surgery.

575
00:34:12.247 --> 00:34:13.613
Me?

576
00:34:13.648 --> 00:34:15.782
Are you sure?

577
00:34:15.817 --> 00:34:19.219
All the faith in the world. old son.

578
00:34:19.253 --> 00:34:21.989
Now. you might want to stand back.

579
00:34:36.155 --> 00:34:38.456
You sure you really want
to go through with this?

580
00:34:38.555 --> 00:34:40.189
It's just a bit of glass.

581
00:34:40.223 --> 00:34:42.024
It's easy to replace.

582
00:34:42.058 --> 00:34:43.992
That's not what I'm talking about.

583
00:34:44.027 --> 00:34:45.994
And you know it.

584
00:34:49.332 --> 00:34:51.466
I can do this.

585
00:35:02.045 --> 00:35:03.579
Right.

586
00:35:05.148 --> 00:35:07.116
I'm off then.

587
00:35:07.850 --> 00:35:11.520
You there! Stop where you are!

588
00:35:39.015 --> 00:35:40.649
Very nice.

589
00:35:40.683 --> 00:35:42.918
And now let's see a plié.

590
00:35:42.952 --> 00:35:45.721
Oh. I think I saw that left heel

591
00:35:45.755 --> 00:35:47.990
wobble a bit. otherwise perfect.

592
00:35:48.024 --> 00:35:51.059
Now. uh... express yourself.

593
00:35:51.094 --> 00:35:53.328
How long's he gonna be under for?

594
00:35:53.363 --> 00:35:55.531
Until the music stops.

595
00:35:56.863 --> 00:35:59.502
The alarm.

596
00:35:59.563 --> 00:36:02.065
How'd you fare?

597
00:36:06.763 --> 00:36:08.799
Attaboy.

598
00:36:08.864 --> 00:36:10.031
I knew I could count on you.

599
00:36:10.065 --> 00:36:11.766
Come on.

600
00:36:13.469 --> 00:36:15.470
Watch that left heel.

601
00:36:32.163 --> 00:36:34.164
Oh. sorry.

602
00:36:35.834 --> 00:36:39.370
- Impressive.
- Should be.

603
00:36:39.404 --> 00:36:41.405
Learned from the best.

604
00:36:58.190 --> 00:37:01.325
By the look on that bloke.
time's not on our side.

605
00:37:01.359 --> 00:37:04.328
The demon will be out of him.
looking for his next victim soon.

606
00:37:04.362 --> 00:37:05.930
We need to get started.

607
00:37:09.835 --> 00:37:11.135
So. what's the plan then?

608
00:37:11.169 --> 00:37:13.103
This demon requires a sacrifice.

609
00:37:13.138 --> 00:37:15.606
That's what I learned from the shaman.

610
00:37:15.640 --> 00:37:18.809
No cage. bottle or vessel can hold it.

611
00:37:18.844 --> 00:37:21.078
Only a body.

612
00:37:21.112 --> 00:37:23.914
A live. human...

613
00:37:23.949 --> 00:37:25.616
body.

614
00:37:27.986 --> 00:37:29.353
Mine.

615
00:37:31.122 --> 00:37:34.024
We could draw straws.

616
00:37:37.195 --> 00:37:40.297
It was your plan all along. wasn't it?

617
00:37:48.573 --> 00:37:51.842
That's why it's just you and me here.

618
00:38:00.218 --> 00:38:02.653
You sneaky bastard.

619
00:38:06.091 --> 00:38:08.058
My chance...

620
00:38:08.093 --> 00:38:11.429
to finally make my life mean something.

621
00:38:12.998 --> 00:38:14.999
It won't be quick.

622
00:38:15.033 --> 00:38:17.134
Could take days of sheer agony

623
00:38:17.169 --> 00:38:19.837
before you die.

624
00:38:19.871 --> 00:38:22.039
And there's no going back.

625
00:38:22.073 --> 00:38:24.408
Do you understand?

626
00:38:28.113 --> 00:38:31.615
There's no better way to go out.

627
00:38:33.051 --> 00:38:34.685
A mage.

628
00:38:34.719 --> 00:38:38.122
Like John Constantine.

629
00:38:43.094 --> 00:38:45.529
I'm proud of you. Gaz.

630
00:38:47.098 --> 00:38:49.266
Truly.

631
00:39:00.245 --> 00:39:02.546
Let's do this.

632
00:39:25.937 --> 00:39:28.572
Alworood...

633
00:39:28.607 --> 00:39:31.275
min alawbee-aa Menemoth

634
00:39:31.309 --> 00:39:35.479
walamrad. meltahema min alnefoos.

635
00:39:35.514 --> 00:39:39.849
weh-yak nastaa-een fi talqe-hey hathehy

636
00:39:39.951 --> 00:39:42.920
alneaam min minwey-et

637
00:39:42.954 --> 00:39:44.655
walarad walhawah

638
00:39:44.689 --> 00:39:47.024
walnar walmeh.

639
00:40:02.274 --> 00:40:04.809
Soltet al-arady almouqdesa

640
00:40:04.843 --> 00:40:08.012
tacht alsamah

641
00:40:08.046 --> 00:40:11.415
fowq tamkeen hathehy altahara

642
00:40:11.450 --> 00:40:13.818
wa-ahsar aley alabad

643
00:40:13.852 --> 00:40:17.555
ra-yeea Menemoth raheeb!

644
00:40:19.024 --> 00:40:21.425
Hold on there. mate!

645
00:40:21.459 --> 00:40:23.027
Not long now.

646
00:40:55.727 --> 00:40:57.162
He's coming around.

647
00:40:57.196 --> 00:40:58.797
We need to get him inside
and into a secure room.

648
00:40:58.831 --> 00:41:01.930
- You put the demon inside of him?
- There was no other way.

649
00:41:02.130 --> 00:41:03.932
You're sacrificing him. you're
sacrificing your friend's life.

650
00:41:04.031 --> 00:41:05.565
It was his choice. And it was a brave one.

651
00:41:05.599 --> 00:41:06.733
You need to respect that.

652
00:41:06.767 --> 00:41:09.669
You manipulated him.
You tricked him into it.

653
00:41:09.703 --> 00:41:11.204
That demon was one of the most powerful

654
00:41:11.238 --> 00:41:12.905
and malevolent entities
I've ever come across.

655
00:41:12.940 --> 00:41:14.674
What we did saved countless lives!

656
00:41:14.708 --> 00:41:15.909
I don't care!

657
00:41:15.943 --> 00:41:17.543
Gary loved you. and you betrayed him!

658
00:41:17.578 --> 00:41:19.545
All he cared about was to make you proud.

659
00:41:19.580 --> 00:41:22.048
And for what. John. huh?

660
00:41:22.082 --> 00:41:23.683
He wanted to be just like you.
Thank God he's not!

661
00:41:23.717 --> 00:41:24.784
He came to me!

662
00:41:26.787 --> 00:41:28.688
You think I wanted this?

663
00:41:28.722 --> 00:41:29.889
Any of it?

664
00:41:31.730 --> 00:41:34.131
I told you this would happen.

665
00:41:34.134 --> 00:41:36.469
People around me die.

666
00:41:36.534 --> 00:41:38.702
If you can't handle it. then go.

667
00:41:45.637 --> 00:41:47.604
Which room do you want to put him in?

668
00:41:49.037 --> 00:41:50.473
Downstairs.

669
00:41:50.537 --> 00:41:52.505
End of the hallway.

